with stored findings showing FAIL on multiple dimensions. Manually write a summary claiming PASS (simulating the bug state). Call the gate verdict computation. Verify it returns FAIL (reading findings) not PASS (reading summary). Repeat with different dimension combinations.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.7,"System":0,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Manual summary text overrides require an explicit override flag and produce an auditable warning record","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is straightforward business logic: absence of a flag should be rejected, presence should trigger audit logging. Unit tests with mock verification of the audit service call are sufficient to catch missing flag validation or missing audit record creation. No storage layer complexity or cross-module orchestration required.","test_description":"Test that calling override-summary without override_flag=True raises a validation error. Test that calling override-summary with override_flag=True and an override_reason succeeds and triggers an audit log with the reason, timestamp, and actor. Verify audit records cannot be created without all required fields.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.65,"Integration":0.35,"System":0,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"After Phase 4 fixes, the review loop cannot finalize PASS unless a fresh review-agent round is executed on the updated diff","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The core failure is in finalization control flow: code must check that review-agent was executed on the current diff before allowing PASS. Integration testing verifies this check happens and blocks finalization when agent hasn't re-run. If the real issue involves agent findings being stale or incorrect, Agentic testing would add confidence, but minimum infrastructure is Integration (verify the